# scope-matching-algorithms

## Core Matching Components (95/100)

Located in `scope-secure/src/lib/scope-mapping.ts`, the scope matching system implements critical algorithms:

1. Guard Length Determination
- Calculates required guard length based on scope physical dimensions
- Maps maximum scope lengths to appropriate guard configurations
- Applies safety margins for proper coverage

2. Mount Height Processing
- Computes mounting height requirements using:
  - Objective lens diameter
  - Tube diameter measurements 
  - Scope body specifications

3. Compatibility Validation
- Enforces scope-guard fit requirements
- Detects non-standard configurations requiring custom orders
- Validates mount diameter compatibility

## Guard Length Thresholds (80/100)

The system defines precise length thresholds in `scope-secure/src/lib/scope-mapping.ts`:

1. Maximum Length Rules
- Maps scope measurements to guard length requirements
- Implements safety margin calculations
- Handles custom length detection

2. Configuration Rules
- Defines standard guard length options
- Specifies measurement tolerances
- Identifies cases requiring custom manufacturing

## Scope Database Integration (85/100)

Implemented in `scope-secure/src/lib/scope-database.ts`:

1. Specification Mapping
- Maintains comprehensive scope measurements database
- Maps physical specifications to mount requirements
- Stores brand-specific configuration rules

2. Search Implementation
- Filters scopes by physical characteristics
- Matches specifications to available guard configurations
- Identifies compatible mounting options

